<mj-text padding="0px 0px 0px 0px"><p class="cutline">Dennis Wanebo works on balance with physical therapist Kristen Kirby at The Corner Boxing Club in Boulder, where non-contact boxing is used as therapy for Parkinson's patients. (John Leyba, Special to the Colorado Sun)</p></mj-text><mj-text>

<p>🌞 It took months for <strong>Jennifer Brown</strong> and <strong>Olivia Prentzel </strong>to get their hands on data that proved what many people in Boulder County knew from their lived experiences: Lots of people, many of them in high school and college, are dying from accidental overdoses of fentanyl. Their three-part series explores how counterfeit prescription medications, laced with deadly amounts of the powerful synthetic opioid, are winding their way through social networks, how some worried parents are taking action where the local health department will not, and how hard it is for prosecutors to prove that selling the pills that led to these deaths is murder. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/15/fentanyl-overdose-boulder-colorado/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

<p>🌞 <strong>David Gilbert</strong> took on a similarly complex topic, reporting for months this summer on people who said they had been sexually assaulted when they were students at the <strong>Colorado Center for the Blind</strong> in Littleton and that when they reported their experiences to the school, were discouraged from making reports to police. Legal experts say the allegations could open the training center to a patterns and practices investigation by the feds. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/18/colorado-center-for-the-blind-sex-assaults/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

<p>🌞 How easy is it to sell your house in Colorado? As simple as asking companies such as <strong>Zillow</strong> and <strong>OpenDoor</strong> to make an offer. That&#8217;s how troubled Zillow ended up owning more than 500 homes in the overheated Front Range market. The company now is trying to unload them, often at prices well below what it paid just weeks before. <strong>Jason Blevins </strong>looked at all those listings to learn whether Zillow&#8217;s fire sale is influencing prices today. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/15/zillow-offers-colorado-homes-front-range/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

<p>🌞 Remember how <strong>Green Bay Packers</strong> quarterback <strong>Aaron Rodgers</strong> didn&#8217;t want to get vaccinated against COVID and then got COVID and wanted to be treated with a monoclonal antibody therapy developed using the exact same science used to develop the vaccine? <strong>John Ingold</strong> talked to public health experts in Colorado who say they&#8217;re counting on precisely that attitude to keep the unvaccinated who get sick out of the hospital. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/18/covid-vaccine-hesitancy-monoclonal-antibodies/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

<p>🌞 Night flying is a rarely used tool in wildland fire fighting. But it&#8217;s easy to understand why, barely a year after the huge East Troublesome and Cameron Peak fires threatened Estes Park, Larimer County&#8217;s sheriff hired an experienced tanker pilot — with more than 1,000 hours of flying using night-vision goggles — to attack the Kruger Rock fire just south of town. <strong>Olivia Prentzel </strong>explains the conditions over the fire that led that pilot, <strong>Mark Thor Olson</strong>, to crash. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/17/pilot-kruger-rock-fire/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

<p>🌞 The battle against the progression of Parkinson&#8217;s disease is often described as a fight. It gets literal, though, at a boxing gym in Boulder where <strong>Kevin Simpson</strong> found people getting relief from their symptoms by mastering non-contact training in the sweet science. &gt;&gt; <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2021/11/18/parkinson-disease-boxing-therapy/?pico=clean"><strong>STORY</strong></a></p>

